<div id="review_764945995" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/764945995" />
    <a title="Buck" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9120555-buck"><img alt="Buck" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1465429605p2/9120555.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/764945995?book_show_action=true">Nov 14, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Buck" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Buck" href="/user/show/9120555-buck">Buck</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780062031433" href="/book/show/17607278-a-dry-white-season">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9120555-buck?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer764945995" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8544959243045561812">This book, about living in South Africa under Apartheid, could be classified as a dystopian novel. The tension continually builds throughout the novel, <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[leading ultimately in a downward spiral to the total destruction of the protagonist. In the epilogue we are left with the feeling that there may be some hope for justice, for the truth to come out, but only in the sense that the evidence survived. <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> In reality, we know that Apartheid did end - and that the events port</span>
  <span id="freeText8544959243045561812" style="display:none">This book, about living in South Africa under Apartheid, could be classified as a dystopian novel. The tension continually builds throughout the novel, <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[leading ultimately in a downward spiral to the total destruction of the protagonist. In the epilogue we are left with the feeling that there may be some hope for justice, for the truth to come out, but only in the sense that the evidence survived. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> In reality, we know that Apartheid did end - and that the events portrayed in this novel can't happen now. They can't, can they? <br /><br />The difference between A Dry White Season and most dystopian novels is that usually the dystopian culture or society or government is fictional. I don't live in South Africa and I haven't experienced Apartheid, but I got the distinct impression that this novel portrayed the kinds of things that could have happened, that were happening. It's Orwellian scary.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8544959243045561812" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


